01/03/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Meeting Monday (28 February), Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and Serbian President Boris Tadic agreed that the Balkans should no longer be the "black hole" of Europe and that the region's future should be focused on economic development.
Buckovski is on a three-day visit to Serbia-Montenegro.
In other news Monday, a NATO inspection team arrived in Skopje for a regular visit aimed at assessing the pace of defence reforms.
The mission is expected to hold talks with senior representatives of the government and army.
(Makfax, A1 TV, Beta - 28/02/05)
